The All Progressives Congress (APC) 2023 presidential aspirant, Rt. Honourable Rotimi Chibuike Amaechi, on Tuesday, commiserated with the government and people of Kano State. DAILY POST reported on Tuesday that several pupils lost their lives in an explosion that rocked the ancient city of Kano The Police Command in Kano State confirmed the death of four persons, claiming that gas, not a bomb exploded on Tuesday morning. Pained by the happening, the National Coordinator, Amaechi Support Group, Comrade Ibrahim Dahiru Danfulani, in a statement said Amaechi Support Group is sad about the unfortunate incident. The group while lamenting that the incident is coming at a time that Nigeria is charged politically with ongoing consultations by aspirants and other national challenges, advised Nigerians to be their brother’s keepers at this crucial time in the nation’s history, at ensuring that peace, brotherliness and respect for one another’s beliefs is adhered to. The statement wished those injured a speedy recovery.